      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BETTOR PUNTER NZ (1) has been racing very well from much tougher barriers, recording back-to-back placings before drawing out but proving too good in a 2.8m win at Cranbourne last time out. Jumps in grade but the ace draw could see him take the next step. SHIFFRIN (8) is a progressive filly who has come from wider on this row to win her last two outings. Did a fine job last time out when successful by 1.4 metres at Geelong. Drawn to enjoy an economical run and with the sprint lane in play could land the hat trick. JET TO HEAVEN (4) resumes after ending last campaign with a series of top-two results. Hasn't raced since October but was readied with a trial. LETS GO LORNA (7) draws wide but will be rock-hard fit after four runs back from a spell and showed some improvement in the latest effort for third at Maryborough.",
